TITLE: Defining JSON Schema Constraints for API Request/Response Structs - Go
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how Go struct tags are used to annotate fields with JSON Schema-specific constraints and documentation, which are then used for both documentation and validation purposes in an API context. Dependencies include Go and typical struct syntax with use of tags such as json, doc, minLength, and maximum. The snippet requires that fields are tagged to specify minimum and maximum values or lengths, and these affect the corresponding generated JSON Schema. Inputs are struct instances with annotated fields; output is the generated schema and enforced request/response validation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/danielgtaylor/huma/blob/main/docs/docs/features/request-validation.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
type Person struct {
    Name string `json:"name" doc:"Person's name" minLength:"1" maxLength:"80"`
    Age  uint   `json:"age,omitempty" doc:"Person's age" maximum:"120"`
}
```

