TITLE: Configuring Security Scheme and Operation in Huma (Go)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set up a bearer token security scheme in the API configuration and apply it to an operation. It shows the process of creating a custom security scheme and adding it to an operation's configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/danielgtaylor/huma/blob/main/docs/docs/features/openapi-generation.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
config := huma.DefaultConfig("My API", "1.0.0")
config.Components.SecuritySchemes = map[string]*huma.SecurityScheme{
		"bearer": {
			Type: "http",
			Scheme: "bearer",
			BearerFormat: "JWT",
		},
	}
api := humachi.New(router, config)

huma.Register(api, huma.Operation{
	OperationID: "get-greeting",
	Method:      http.MethodGet,
	Path:        "/greeting/{name}",
	Summary:     "Get a greeting",
	Security: []map[string][]string{
		{"bearer": {}},
	},
}, func(ctx context.Context, input *GreetingInput) (*GreetingOutput, error) {
	// ...
})
```

