TITLE: Enabling Struct and Field Nullability in JSON Schema - Go
DESCRIPTION: These Go struct examples illustrate various approaches to making fields or entire structs nullable within the generated JSON Schema, such as using nullable tags or pointer types. The first struct shows how the presence of a field named '_' with nullable:true makes the entire struct nullable, while the second struct demonstrates making scalar fields nullable through pointer types or explicit nullable:true tags. A constraint is that nullability for maps and structs at the field level is not supported (struct-level nullability must be used). These patterns determine whether the generated schema allows 'null' as a value, impacting how validation behaves for absent or null fields in incoming API data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/danielgtaylor/huma/blob/main/docs/docs/features/request-validation.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// Make an entire struct (not its fields) nullable.
type MyStruct1 struct {
    _ struct{} `nullable:"true"`
    Field1 string `json:"field1"`
    Field2 string `json:"field2"`
}

// Make a specific scalar field nullable. This is *not* supported for
// maps or structs. Structs *must* use the method above.
type MyStruct2 struct {
    Field1 *string `json:"field1"`
    Field2 string `json:"field2" nullable:"true"`
}
```

