TITLE: Passing Options via Command-Line and Environment Variables - Go CLI in Bash
DESCRIPTION: This bash snippet demonstrates how to pass configuration options to the Go CLI service via command-line flags or environment variables. It gives usage for long and short-form arguments, and sets environment variables with the SERVICE_ prefix for option binding. The Go binary must be available, and environment variables take precedence unless overridden by flags.
