TITLE: Implementing Custom Wrapper for Optional Parameters in Go
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a custom wrapper type for handling optional query parameters, implementing necessary interfaces for Huma integration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/danielgtaylor/huma/blob/main/docs/docs/features/request-inputs.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
type OptionalParam[T any] struct {
	Value T
	IsSet bool
}

func (o OptionalParam[T]) Schema(r huma.Registry) *huma.Schema {
	return huma.SchemaFromType(r, reflect.TypeOf(o.Value))
}

func (o *OptionalParam[T]) Receiver() reflect.Value {
	return reflect.ValueOf(o).Elem().Field(0)
}

func (o *OptionalParam[T]) OnParamSet(isSet bool, parsed any) {
	o.IsSet = isSet
}

type MyRequestInput struct {
    MaybeText OptionalParam[string] `query:"text"`
}
```
